<h2>Introduction</h2>
 <p>Welcome to Chameleon, the Adaptive Integrated Development Environment.</p>

 <h3><a name="purpose">What is Chameleon?</a></h3>
  <p>Chameleon is an Integrated Development Environment (IDE for short).  It is a single program that combines programming tools and functions into one unified environment to assist in code development.</p>

 <h3><a name="scope">When or Why Do I Use it?</a></h3>
  <p>Chameleon is designed for, and most appropriate for beginning C/C++ programmers in an instructional environment.</p>

 <h3><a name="definitions">Who wrote it?</a></h3>
  <p>Chameleon was designed and written by Mark Erikson, Ben Carhart, and David Czechowski as their senior design project during the 2003-2004 school year at Cedarville University.  Mark resumed active development on version 1.1+ in October 2006.</p>


